From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000001 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Bruno Castelló <bfcastello@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 6 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] drivers/vga: inject vgpu3d properties into ATI PCI node

Injects device-tree properties into the ATY,Rage128Pd Name Registry node
during NDRV installation:

  "driver-reg-properties"  (integer 1) -- unconditional
    Mac OS 9 ATI extensions (ATIMM, ATI 3D Accelerator) require this
    property to enable their 3D acceleration code paths.

  "qemu,vgpu3d"     (string "true") -- conditional on MMIO magic
  "qemu,vgpu3d-ver" (integer 1)     -- conditional on MMIO magic
    Signals vgpu3d passthrough transport is active (requires QEMU
    patches 0003/0004). If the magic register reads 0 (vanilla QEMU),
    the branch is not taken and no transport properties are injected.

TOKENIZER FIX (why rl@ instead of le-l@):

  le-l@ and le-w@ are bound via bind_func() in libopenbios/init.c.
  They are absent from the fcode-utils tokenizer dictionary. vga.fs is
  compiled by toke into QEMU,VGA.bin (see drivers/build.xml), so any
  word absent from the tokenizer causes: "Word le-l@ is not in dictionary"

  rl@ is a standard IEEE 1275 FCode primitive encoded by token number --
  always present in the tokenizer dictionary.

BYTE-SWAP MATH:

  The vgpu3d control register region is DEVICE_LITTLE_ENDIAN (ati.c).
  When the big-endian PPC CPU reads from this region via rl@:
    1. C read handler returns 0x56475033 ("VGP3").
    2. QEMU byte-swaps for BE CPU: 0x56475033 -> 0x33504756.
    3. rl@ (native PPC load) sees 0x33504756.
  Compare against h# 33504756, not h# 56475033.

REGISTER MAP (BAR2 layout, QEMU patch 0003):

  BAR2 + h#4000  vgpu3d control registers
    +h#00  VGPU3D_REG_DOORBELL  (WO)
    +h#04  VGPU3D_REG_TAIL      (RO)
    +h#08  VGPU3D_REG_MAGIC     (RO)  h#56475033 "VGP3"
    +h#0C  VGPU3D_REG_VERSION   (RO)  protocol version

  Magic probe address: mmio-addr + h#4000 + h#08 = mmio-addr + h#4008

Signed-off-by: Bruno Castelló <bfcastello@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/vga.fs | 14 ++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 14 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/vga.fs b/drivers/vga.fs
--- a/drivers/vga.fs
+++ b/drivers/vga.fs
@@ -247,6 +247,20 @@ : qemu-vga-driver-install ( -- )
   mmio-addr -1 = if
     map-mmio vbe-init
   then
+
+  \ Mac OS 9 ATI extensions (ATIMM, ATI 3D Accelerator) require this.
+  1 encode-int " driver-reg-properties" property
+
+  \ Probe vgpu3d passthrough (needs QEMU patch 0003). rl@ is tokenizer-safe;
+  \ le-l@ is bind_func runtime-only (absent from toke dictionary).
+  \ DEVICE_LITTLE_ENDIAN region: h#56475033 arrives byte-swapped as h#33504756.
+  mmio-addr -1 <> if
+    mmio-addr h# 4008 + rl@ h# 33504756 = if
+      1 encode-int " qemu,vgpu3d-ver" property
+      " true" encode-string " qemu,vgpu3d" property
+    then
+  then
+
   fb-addr -1 = if
     map-fb fb-addr to frame-buffer-adr
     default-font set-font
